## Context
After PR #82, ticket-new has disable-model-invocation: false while start-ticket
uses true. The two skills are peers in the ticket lifecycle; the inconsistency
may be intentional (ticket-new needs LLM to extract intent from free-form input)
or an oversight. Worth a deliberate decision before the next skill refactor.

## Actions
1. Read skills/ticket-new/SKILL.md and skills/start-ticket/SKILL.md.
2. Determine whether ticket-new genuinely requires model invocation (free-form
   input parsing) or could run without it.
3. If the difference is intentional, add a comment to ticket-new's frontmatter
   explaining why. If not, align both to the correct value.

## Test
Both skill files have a deliberate, consistent disable-model-invocation value
with reasoning documented if they differ.

## Exit criteria
No unexplained inconsistency between disable-model-invocation values across
ticket-* skills.
